### Description

#### Issue
Calling setCenter method on a `google.maps.Map` object breaks with following error message

> TypeError: setCenter is not a function

I more or less followed the Autocomplete Places guide on developers.google.com: https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/examples/places-autocomplete

This is the error
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28787596/197398492-3a55fcca-04b4-4ff2-8945-ecc78d66d72a.png)


---
#### Versions
```
"@angular/core": "~13.0.0"
"@angular/google-maps": "^13.3.9"
```

Below is the part of the sample that I have in place.

I lazily load google maps and once done, I add a listener to the `google.maps.places.Autocomplete` - `place_changed`

When the input changes, this function gets executed without issues. However, calling `setCenter` with a valid `latLng` object fails.

#### Module
```
imports: [
    GoogleMapsModule,
    HttpClientModule,
    HttpClientJsonpModule,
]
```

#### Component Html
```
<google-map #mapRef [options]="options" [center]="center"></google-map>
```

#### Component Typescript
```
googleMapsLoaded: Observable<boolean>;
@ViewChild('mapRef') mapRef: google.maps.Map;
@ViewChild('addressInputRef') addressInputRef: any;
center: google.maps.LatLngLiteral = {
    lat: 25.0893271,
    lng: 55.1458288
  };

  options: google.maps.MapOptions = {
    zoom: 15
  }

ngAfterViewInit(): void {
    this.googleMapsLoaded = this.httpClient.jsonp(
      'https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=my-key&libraries=places',
      'callback').pipe(
      map(() => {
        let autocomplete = new google.maps.places.Autocomplete(
          this.addressInputRef.nativeElement
        );

        autocomplete.addListener('place_changed', () => {
          let place = autocomplete.getPlace();

          if (!place.geometry || !place.geometry.location) {
            return;
          }

          // here I get the place.geometry.location without issues, but setCenter breaks
          // I also tried instantiating a new google.maps.LatLng, but same issue
          this.mapRef.setCenter(place.geometry.location);
        });

        return true;
      }), catchError(() => of(false)),
    );
  }
```                          





### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
1. Follow code in issue description
2. or follow https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/examples/places-autocomplete


### Expected Behavior

I expect the map to refresh with the new latLng position

### Actual Behavior

setCenter throws `TypeError: this.mapRef.setCenter is not a function`

